derivative equation.

00:49:40.270 --> 00:49:43.170
So let's try to find
an equation that

00:49:43.170 --> 00:49:47.830
is satisfied by the Heisenberg
operator rather than a formula.

00:49:47.830 --> 00:49:50.150
You'll say, well,
this is better.

00:49:50.150 --> 00:49:54.996
But the fact is that seldom you
know U. And even if you know U,

00:49:54.996 --> 00:49:59.010
you have to do this
simplification, which is hard.

00:49:59.010 --> 00:50:03.080
So finding a differential
equation for the operator

00:50:03.080 --> 00:50:04.090
is useful.

00:50:04.090 --> 00:50:11.300
So differential equation
